##Bio

Meet Dr. Ikechukwu (Ike) Onwuka, an expert in environmental data science. His research focuses on analyzing the interactions between nutrients, sediment, and water in aquatic environments like rivers, canals, and wetlands. Using surrogate measurements, Dr. Onwuka develops estimates of water quality measurements with high temporal resolution. He also applies data science tools to identify patterns in aquatic systems, which he uses to make predictions for water resource management. Additionally, Dr. Onwuka is passionate about using data science to connect water, aquatic sciences, climate change, and food security to promote environmental sustainability. He is eager to collaborate with industry, academia, and international organizations like the United Nations and World Bank.

## Education

